</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 9:54:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1714.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hm ok</span><hr size=1> Well you can gain aggro with any spell if you cast it often enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and of course you can cast Scars VERY often in a given time frame <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but with reasonable usage you can use Scars all time and never get aggro.<br>
<br>
The fast casting time makes Scars my favourite spell for greenie farming. Loved to use it to blast shard wurms to death with it in GD (while my pet was fighting other wurms), you should try that!<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
